{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: composition-eu-hdr_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Composition instance conforming to the CompositionEuHdr
    profile (HL7 Europe Hospital Discharge Report). Structurally very similar
    to composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig but with four meaningful differences
    described below.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: CompositionEuHdr
    Fixed elements:
      type.coding  = $loinc#34105-7 "Hospital Discharge summary"
      status       = #final
      title        = "Hospital Discharge Report"
      confidentiality = #N

  DIFFERENCES FROM composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig
    See the full comparison table in composition-eu-eps_fsh.twig. The four
    behavioural differences specific to this HDR template are:

    1. CUSTODIAN VARIABLE
       Uses `provider.instanceorganization` (not `provider.instanceroleorg`).
       The variable name difference reflects a different field on the provider
       object depending on the document context.

    2. text.status = #empty POSITION — BEFORE THE SECTIONS LOOP
       The Composition-level narrative is declared BEFORE the sections loop,
       unlike EPS where it appears at the end. This has no effect on the FSH
       output (SUSHI processes rules, not their order within the instance), but
       it means the `text.*` rules appear in the compiled FSH before all
       section rules, which may affect human readability of the output.

    3. UNNAMED SECTION SUPPORT — CONDITIONAL SLICE NAME
       Each section is checked for an empty slicename:
         {% if slicename is empty %}
         * section[+]
         {% else %}
         * section[{{ slicename }}]
         {% endif %}
       When `slicename` is an empty string key in the `sections` dict, an
       unnamed append `[+]` is used. This allows some sections to be generic
       (not constrained to a named slice) while others are profile-defined.
       EPS always requires a named slice.

    4. SECTION FSH RAW INJECTION — SECOND PASS LOOP
       After the main sections loop, a second loop iterates over `sections`
       again — this time as a simple value iteration (without a key variable)
       — and injects any pre-built FSH strings stored on each section:
         {% for section in sections %}
         {% if section.fsh is not empty %}
         {{ section.fsh | raw }}
         {% endif %}
         {% endfor %}
       `section.fsh` is a pre-formatted FSH string (e.g. additional rules
       that cannot be expressed through the standard entry loop) injected
       verbatim with `| raw`. This allows sections to carry arbitrary FSH
       content generated upstream by the PHP caller.
       Note: the first loop uses `for slicename, section in sections` (key-value
       form); the second uses `for section in sections` (value-only form). On a
       PHP associative array, the value-only form iterates the values in
       insertion order.

    5. ENTRY SLICE VARIABLE NAME
       The entry slice name local variable is `bundleentryslicename` (not
       `sectionentryslicename` as in EPS). Both serve identical purposes and
       produce identical FSH output — the difference is only in the Twig
       variable name. This is a naming inconsistency between the two templates.

  SECTION OBJECT STRUCTURE
    Same as EPS, with the addition of:
    ┌───────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Field                         │ Type     │ Description                                  │
    ├───────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ fsh                           │ string?  │ Optional pre-built FSH string to inject      │
    │                               │          │ verbatim after the main sections loop.       │
    │                               │          │ Used with \| raw. Not present in EPS.        │
    └───────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────────────┘
    All other section fields (title, code, display, text, indicateEmptyListReason,
    entries) are identical to the EPS structure.

  ENTRY OBJECT STRUCTURE
    Identical to EPS, except the local Twig variable for the slice name is
    called `bundleentryslicename` instead of `sectionentryslicename`.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                         │ Type     │ Description                                    │
  ├──────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ composition.instanceid           │ string   │ UUID for the Composition resource.             │
  │ composition.identifier           │ string   │ Business identifier value.                     │
  │ composition.date                 │ date     │ Document date; filtered to ISO 8601 UTC.       │
  │ patient.instanceid               │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource.                  │
  │ patient.name                     │ string   │ Full display name.                             │
  │ patient.age                      │ string   │ Pre-computed age string for Description only.  │
  │ provider.instancerole            │ string   │ UUID of the author PractitionerRole.           │
  │ provider.instanceorganization    │ string   │ UUID of the custodian Organisation.            │
  │                                  │          │ Note: NOT instanceroleorg (differs from EPS).  │
  │ sections                         │ dict     │ Associative array: slicename → section object. │
  │                                  │          │ Empty string key → unnamed [+] section.        │
  │   [slicename].fsh                │ string?  │   Optional raw FSH string (HDR-specific).      │
  │   [slicename].title              │ string   │   (all other fields same as EPS)               │
  └──────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  GLOBAL VARIABLES USED
    HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID — OID root for the Composition identifier system URI.

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    $loinc          — 34105-7 "Hospital Discharge summary"
    $list-empty-reason — #nilknown (empty section reason)

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2026-03-01
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Composition-" ~ composition.instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: CompositionEuHdr
Title: "HL7 Europe Hospital Discharge Report (HDR) Composition"
{# patientdisplay set inline between FSH header lines — see EPS template for full explanation #}
{% set patientdisplay = patient.name ~ " (" ~ patient.age ~ " y/o) - synthetic data" %}
Description: "Complete HL7 Europe Hospital Discharge Report (HDR) FHIR Composition example for {{ patientdisplay }}"
Usage: #inline

{# Inject synthetic-data governance meta tags #}
{{ syntheticDataPolicyMeta() | raw }}

* id = "{{ composition.instanceid }}"

{# Composition business identifier under the HL7 Europe OID namespace #}
* identifier.system = "urn:oid:{{ HL7EUROPEEXAMPLESOID }}"
* identifier.value = "{{ composition.identifier }}"
* identifier.assigner.display = "HL7 Europe"

* title = "Hospital Discharge Report"
* status = #final

{# Fixed LOINC type: Hospital Discharge summary #}
* type.coding = $loinc#34105-7 "Hospital Discharge summary"
* type.text = "Hospital Discharge Report"

* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{# Author: PractitionerRole (same variable as EPS) #}
* author[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ provider.instancerole }})

{#
  Custodian: uses `provider.instanceorganization` — differs from EPS which
  uses `provider.instanceroleorg`. Different field name, same intent.
#}
* custodian[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ provider.instanceorganization }})

{# Date: same ISO 8601 UTC format as EPS #}
* date = "{{ composition.date|date('Y-m-d\\TH:i:s\\Z') }}"

* confidentiality = #N

{#
  ── Composition-level narrative — placed BEFORE sections ─────────────────────
  Differs from EPS where text.status = #empty appears at the end.
  Position has no FSH/FHIR semantic effect; affects only output readability.
#}
* text.status = #empty
* text.div = "<div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">intentionally left empty / not meaningful</div>"

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  SECTIONS LOOP — key-value dict iteration (same pattern as EPS)
  Additional HDR feature: conditional unnamed section support.
  When slicename (the dict key) is an empty string, section[+] is used.
  When slicename is non-empty, section[{{ slicename }}] is used.
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% set sectioncount = 0 %} {# counter for debugging; not used in FSH output #}

{% for slicename, section in sections %}

{% set sectioncount = sectioncount + 1 %}
// section, slice {{ slicename }}
//
{#
  Conditional slice: empty slicename → unnamed [+] append;
  non-empty slicename → named slice. This allows generic sections alongside
  profile-defined named ones, unlike EPS which always requires a named slice.
#}
{% if slicename is empty %}
* section[+]
{% else %}
* section[{{ slicename }}]
{% endif %}
  * title = "{{ section.title }}"
  * code = {{ section.code }} "{{ section.display }}"
  * text.status = #generated
  * text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
{{ section.text | raw }}
</div>
"""

{# Empty section sentinel — identical to EPS #}
{% if section.indicateEmptyListReason is not empty and section.indicateEmptyListReason == "TRUE" %}

  * emptyReason = $list-empty-reason#nilknown

{% else %}

{#
  Entries loop — same logic as EPS except local variable is named
  `bundleentryslicename` (not `sectionentryslicename` as in EPS).
  Both produce identical FSH output; the name difference is cosmetic.
#}
{% for entry in section.entries %}

{% if entry.bundleentryslicename is empty %}
{% set bundleentryslicename = "" %}
{% else %}
{% set bundleentryslicename = "[" ~ entry.bundleentryslicename ~ "]" %}
{% endif %}

{% if entry.nosectionentry is empty or entry.nosectionentry != "TRUE" %}
  * entry{{ bundleentryslicename }}[+] = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ entry.id }})
{% endif %}

{% endfor %} {# entries #}

{% endif %} {# empty reason / entries #}

{% endfor %} {# sections — first pass: slice names + entries #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  SECTION FSH RAW INJECTION — second pass loop (HDR-only feature)
  Iterates sections a second time as a simple value loop (no key variable)
  to inject any pre-built FSH strings stored on each section object.
  `section.fsh` is a pre-formatted FSH string produced upstream by the PHP
  caller and injected verbatim with | raw.
  Use case: FSH rules that cannot be expressed through the standard entry
  loop pattern (e.g. deeply nested sub-elements, additional slice bindings).
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#}
{% for section in sections %}
{% if section.fsh is not empty %}
{{ section.fsh | raw }}
{% endif %}
{% endfor %} {# sections — second pass: raw FSH injection #}

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor — intentionally empty #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
{# HTML bag is never populated in this template; emitHTML() returns empty string #}
